result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 15CF26, 15CF85 & 15CF88 Cases called @ 1:43 p.m. Defendant Jordan J. Imm in court with attorney Ben Szilagyi.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea: 15CF26 - Ct 2: Guilty. 15CF88 - Ct 1: Guilty. Court accepts plea and enters JOC. 15CF88 - Ct 1: Repeater enhancer dismissed. 15CF26 - Ct 1: DRI. 15CF85 - Cts 1 & 2 - DRI. 15CF88 - Cts 2 & 3: DRI. Uncharged referral for Felony Bail Jumping stemming from a new charge in Winnebago Co 15CM956 occuring on July 10, 2015 dismissed and read in. No statement by DE. Court orders: S/W - 3 years probation - Conditions: 15CF26 only - 90 days WCJ - Huber, No GT, 1 day CFTS - Sentence to commence by no later than 2/1/16.  As to both counts -  $100 Restitution to the Waushara County Sheriff's Department to be paid by no later than June 1, 2016, defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician, AODA and follow through, Defendant to obtain a GED or HSED, NC w/ F. Loose, Costs to include DNA surcharge w/ 60 DTP or PP.  Appeal rights given.

BOND ORDERED AS TO WAUSHARA CO CASE NOS. 2015CF000085 AND 2015CF000088.  The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.

15CF-26, 15CF-85 and 15CF-88 - All 3 Cases called at 1:10 PM: Defendant Jordan J. Imm in court, in custody, with attorney Ben Szilagyi, both appearing via video.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  15CF-85 and 15CF-88:  Complaints Stated - receipt admitted - reading waived.  Per SPD:  Eligibility Confirmed.
